# IMAGE QUALITY SETTING (Still Photography)

## Copying Custom Settings

Copy custom settings from one bank to another, overwriting the settings in the destination bank. If the source bank has been renamed, the name will also be copied to the destination bank.

1. **Select**  
   Go to **IMAGE QUALITY SETTING** > **EDIT/SAVE CUSTOM SETTING** in the shooting menu and press **MENU/OK**.

   > To save settings for movie recording, navigate to **MOVIE SETTING** in the movie menus and select **EDIT/SAVE CUSTOM SETTING**.

2. **Highlight the Source Bank**  
   Highlight the source bank and press **MENU/OK**.

   !Source Bank Selection

3. **Highlight COPY**  
   Highlight **COPY** and press **MENU/OK**.

   !Copy Option

4. **Highlight the Destination Bank**  
   Highlight the destination bank (C1 through C7) and press **MENU/OK**. A confirmation dialog will be displayed.

   > Any changes to custom settings in the destination bank will be overwritten.

   !Destination Bank Selection

5. **Confirm and Copy**  
   Highlight **OK** and press **MENU/OK**. The selected settings will be copied to the destination bank, overwriting any existing settings.

   !Confirmation Dialog
